<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>you could use socket.io to create a bidirectional connection with your server, and update your list each time something new pop's up</p>

<p>and if you're new to the server, take a look at my blog:
<a href="https://mathieuauclairweb.wordpress.com/2017/05/02/how-to-make-a-nodejs-server-with-to-database-part-1/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://mathieuauclairweb.wordpress.com/2017/05/02/how-to-make-a-nodejs-server-with-to-database-part-1/</a></p>

<p>I might add a tutorial on how to use socket.io this afternoon </p>
    </div>
